# Copy to .env.local and fill in values (see README.md).

# Local WhatsApp webhook: `npm run dev` → optional tunnel; point callback at /api/webhooks/whatsapp.
# Use DATABASE_URL_DEVELOPMENT for a Neon dev branch so webhook tests do not touch production Postgres.

# Optional — ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 default region for parsing national-format phones (libphonenumber).
# Server: PHONE_DEFAULT_COUNTRY. Browser (new order form): NEXT_PUBLIC_PHONE_DEFAULT_COUNTRY (same value).
# PHONE_DEFAULT_COUNTRY=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_PHONE_DEFAULT_COUNTRY=

# Neon Postgres — production / default pool URL (`next start`, Vercel production). Never point this at dev data when deployed.
DATABASE_URL=

# Neon dev branch URL for local `npm run dev` and non-production tooling. When unset, DATABASE_URL is used everywhere.
# Create a branch in Neon Console (or MCP) named e.g. `development`, paste its pooled URI here — run `npm run db:migrate` against it once.
DATABASE_URL_DEVELOPMENT=

# Slice of product surface: unset or `standard` → full navigation; `core` → reduced nav (campaigns/meta-engagement available with Meta env).
FEATURE_SET=

# Meta Conversions API — server-side Purchase from createOrder (lib/meta-capi.ts → Graph API).
# Use a System User access token with ads_management (or events manager–appropriate scope).
META_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# Events Manager dataset id for CAPI (Graph `/{dataset_id}/events`). For CTWA, run `npm run meta:waba-dataset`.
META_DATASET_ID=
# Optional alias read by CAPI helpers (same value as Events Manager dataset / pixel-backed dataset id).
# META_PIXEL_ID=
# Fallback WABA when a CTWA session row has no waba_id (older rows). Prefer `waba_id` from webhook `entry.id` on each session.
META_WHATSAPP_BUSINESS_ACCOUNT_ID=

# Events Manager → Test events code. Required when NODE_ENV is not production (CAPI uses TestEvent + test_event_code). Ignored in production (live Purchase only).
META_TEST_EVENT_CODE=

# Meta webhooks — ONE verify string for every callback URL below (paste the same in Meta’s “Verify token” fields).
# Set any one of: META_WEBHOOK_VERIFY_TOKEN (recommended single name), or META_WHATSAPP_VERIFY_TOKEN, or META_PAGE_WEBHOOK_VERIFY_TOKEN.
META_WEBHOOK_VERIFY_TOKEN=
# META_WHATSAPP_VERIFY_TOKEN=
# META_PAGE_WEBHOOK_VERIFY_TOKEN=
META_APP_SECRET=
# Instagram Graph API app (if different from Page app): App settings → Basic → App secret — used to verify webhooks signed by that app (tried before META_APP_SECRET).
# META_INSTAGRAM_APP_SECRET=
# Legacy alias for the same value:
# META_INSTAGRAM_LOGIN_APP_SECRET=
# Optional — Chakra pass-through: HMAC-SHA256(raw body) hex in X-Chakra-Signature-256 (no sha256= prefix).
# If META_APP_SECRET is also set, this route accepts POSTs when either X-Chakra-Signature-256 or X-Hub-Signature-256 verifies.
# If the value contains # or $, wrap it in double quotes in .env.local (unquoted # truncates the secret).
# CHAKRA_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# Outbound WhatsApp (Graph send API) — same WABA as webhooks; used by the sales agent.
# WHATSAPP_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# WHATSAPP_PHONE_NUMBER_ID=
# Optional fallback token name (lib/whatsapp-send.ts tries this after WHATSAPP_ACCESS_TOKEN).
# META_WHATSAPP_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# Sales agent (inbound text → OpenAI → optional WhatsApp send). Off unless explicitly enabled.
# SALES_AGENT_ENABLED=false
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# When false, replies are only stored in Postgres (no Graph send API).
# SALES_AGENT_SEND_WHATSAPP=false
# Optional — create/update contacts from non-CTWA WhatsApp profile names.
# SALES_AGENT_UPSERT_CONTACT=false
# Optional — overrides default store name «افغان آنلاین» in the sales agent prompt.
# SALES_AGENT_BRAND_NAME=

# Staff JWT sign-in (`staff_session` cookie). Sign in at /login. Unauthenticated access is only / (landing), /orders/new, /orders/*/confirmation, and webhooks.
# Generate a long random string (32+ chars), e.g. openssl rand -base64 32
AUTH_SECRET=
# Create operators: npm run staff:create-user -- email@example.com 'password'
# Requires DATABASE_URL and applied migration 0020_staff_users.

# Meta Marketing API — campaigns / ad insights / Marketing API activity archive (/campaigns UI).
# META_ACCESS_TOKEN needs ads_read (Insights + GET act_{id}/activities activity log).
# META_AD_ACCOUNT_ID=
# Optional Graph version override (default v22.0)
# META_GRAPH_VERSION=v22.0

# Campaign cockpit (/campaigns) — rule thresholds for COD verdicts (optional; sensible defaults in code).
# CAMPAIGN_MIN_SPEND_TO_JUDGE=25
# CAMPAIGN_MIN_CTWA_SESSIONS_TO_JUDGE=15
# CAMPAIGN_MIN_PAID_ORDERS_TO_SCALE=3
# Effective CPA cap: dynamic (net profit ÷ converted orders ÷ CAMPAIGN_CPA_CAP_PROFIT_DIVISOR) when that yields positive $/order, else CAMPAIGN_ABSOLUTE_MAX_CPA_PAID_ORDER
# CAMPAIGN_ABSOLUTE_MAX_CPA_PAID_ORDER=35
# CAMPAIGN_CPA_CAP_PROFIT_DIVISOR=1.1
# CAMPAIGN_TARGET_PROFIT_ROAS=1.5
# CAMPAIGN_KILL_SPEND_WITH_ZERO_PAID_ORDERS=50
# CAMPAIGN_MAX_PENDING_REVENUE_SHARE=0.55
# CAMPAIGN_MIN_ORDER_CONV_FROM_CTWA=0.02
# CAMPAIGN_MIN_PAID_CONV_FROM_CTWA=0.01
# CAMPAIGN_OPTIMIZE_SPEND_FLOOR=20
# Engagement / Meta delivery (optional signals — quality & frequency need Meta fields wired separately)
# CAMPAIGN_MIN_SPEND_ENGAGEMENT_QUALITY=30
# CAMPAIGN_MIN_CTR=0.005
# CAMPAIGN_MIN_OUTBOUND_CTR=0.003
# CAMPAIGN_MIN_QUALITY_RANK_SCORE=0.3
# CAMPAIGN_MAX_AVG_FREQUENCY=2.5
# CAMPAIGN_MIN_FIRST_IMPRESSION_RATIO=0.7
# CAMPAIGN_MAX_DAILY_PROFIT_CV=0.7
# CAMPAIGN_MIN_PAID_ORDERS_FOR_CONFIDENCE=12
# CAMPAIGN_MIN_ROAS_LOWER_BOUND=1.1
# CAMPAIGN_MAX_RETURN_RATE=0.15
# CAMPAIGN_MAX_DAYS_PENDING_INCREASE=2
#
# Optional COD economics on `orders`: delivery_cost, return_cost, cod_fee (migration 0022).
# Set via SQL/API when you track fulfillment; gross profit on /campaigns subtracts these for paid orders only.
#
# Ad insights (0023 + 0031): actions-derived messaging/purchases; plus frequency + quality_ranking on sync (first-time share not on Insights fields API for this query).
# Run `npm run db:migrate` then Sync from Meta on /campaigns to backfill.

# Business KB for the agent lives in Postgres (`business_knowledge`); edit at /sales/knowledge (requires login).

# --- Meta Page + Instagram engagement (/meta-engagement, /api/webhooks/meta) ---
# Long-lived Page access token with:
#   • Page: pages_manage_engagement, pages_manage_posts, pages_read_engagement, pages_show_list, pages_messaging
#   • instagram_manage_comments, instagram_manage_messages (IG comments + DM bridge), instagram_basic (often bundled with IG prod)
# App Review: explain comment moderation + optional DM bridge that redirects to WhatsApp (transactional, user-initiated).
# Webhook callback: https://<host>/api/webhooks/meta — use the SAME verify token as WhatsApp (see META_WEBHOOK_VERIFY_TOKEN above).
# Webhook POST signatures: set META_APP_SECRET for your primary Meta app; if Instagram uses a separate Graph API app, set META_INSTAGRAM_APP_SECRET to that app’s Basic → App secret (server verifies with Instagram secret first, then META_APP_SECRET).
# Debug: log full parsed webhook JSON to the server console (do not enable in production).
# META_WEBHOOK_DEBUG=true
# One-line log per verified POST (object + size): on in dev; set META_WEBHOOK_TRACE=true in production.
# META_WEBHOOK_TRACE=true
# If POST webhooks never arrive: (1) Graph bundle — npm run meta:subscribe-webhooks (app Page subscription + Page subscribed_apps + IG Dashboard reminder) or separately META_APP_ID + META_PAGE_WEBHOOK_CALLBACK_URL + npm run meta:app-webhook-subscribe then npm run meta:subscribe-page-webhooks -- <PAGE_ID> (2) Instagram object fields — App Dashboard only (comments/messages); checklist: npm run meta:instagram-webhooks -- <PAGE_ID>
# Reachability (DNS + HTTPS via Node): npm run meta:webhook-health
# Signed POST of Dashboard-style `{ sample }` JSON (proves callback + secrets locally): npm run meta:webhook-send-sample
# META_APP_ID=
# Full URL Meta calls for Page + WhatsApp-style webhooks (include /api/webhooks/meta; do not use origin-only here).
# META_PAGE_WEBHOOK_CALLBACK_URL=https://your-host.example/api/webhooks/meta
# META_APP_PAGE_WEBHOOK_FIELDS=messages,feed
# META_FACEBOOK_PAGE_ID=          ← Facebook Page id (Messenger + Page feed webhooks; npm run meta:subscribe-page-webhooks).
# META_INSTAGRAM_BUSINESS_ACCOUNT_ID=   ← Instagram professional account id — object "instagram" webhooks + Dashboard sample normalization (optional helper: npm run meta:instagram-webhooks -- <PAGE_ID>).
# Optional: Page webhook fields for subscribe script (default messages,feed). Use feed only if messages fails without pages_messaging.
# META_SUBSCRIBE_PAGE_FIELDS=messages,feed
# In-app Graph (comments / Messenger send): uses META_PAGE_ACCESS_TOKEN if set, otherwise META_ACCESS_TOKEN.
# Page webhook subscribe script: prefers META_PAGE_ACCESS_TOKEN; otherwise resolves Page token via GET /me/accounts using a **user** META_ACCESS_TOKEN (New Pages rejects user token on subscribed_apps directly).
# META_PAGE_ACCESS_TOKEN=
#
# DM bridge (Messenger + IG DM): single AI reply per thread with mandatory WhatsApp link.
# WHATSAPP_REDIRECT_URL=
# Optional overrides:
# DM_BRIDGE_ENABLED=
# DM_BRIDGE_OPENAI_MODEL=
# DM_BRIDGE_SYSTEM_PROMPT_APPEND=
# DM_BRIDGE_BRAND_NAME=
#
# Optional: AI draft suggestions for public comments (staff reviews before send).
# META_COMMENT_SUGGEST_MODEL=
# META_COMMENT_SUGGEST_BRAND=
